      "side": 1,
      "message": "i considered this. it requires complicating MessageWriter (which is currently just a json.Encoder, iirc), and it probably doesn\u0027t give much benefit: there\u0027s usually synchronization when writing control messages, since ordering is important. testing.State\u0027s log/error methods pass messages back through a channel, and adding synchronization here feels like the other part of that. if there are races in the bundle/runner code that writes control messages, then that\u0027s probably a bigger problem since the messages may arrive in an unexpected order, and adding synchronization to MessageWriter won\u0027t help with that.\n\nplease let me know if you feel strongly, though. :-)",
